co.louiscap.lib.compat.string

Class StringChunker

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.louiscap.lib.compat.string.StringChunker

  • public class StringChunker
extends java.lang.Object
    A class for stepping through a string and returning certain elements ("chunks") of it

      • reverse

        public void reverse(int length)
        Step backwards from the current position by the specified distance. If this operation would cause the position of the StringChunker to be a negative value, it is set to 0 instead.
        Parameters:
        length - The distance to travel back along the source string (towards index 0)

      • skip

        public void skip(int length)
        Step forward through the source String by the specified distance, ignoring anything that is passed over. If this operation would cause the position of the StringChunker to be set past the last index of the source String, it is set to target the last index instead.
        Parameters:
        length - The distance to travel forward along the source String (towards index source.length()).

      • getUntil

        public java.lang.String getUntil(java.lang.String needle)
        Collects everything at the start of the string until it encounters the given needle, and returns all that has been collected. This version of the method skips over the needle so that the next action is performed at the end of the target string (analogous to calling getUntil(String, boolean) with false as the second parameter). Increments StringChunker position
        Parameters:
        needle - The target string to search for. Acts as a delimiter.
        Returns:
        A String containing every character in the string until the needle is found. If the needle is not found, or it is null, the String will contain every character from the current position of the chunker until the end of the source String.

      • getUntil

        public java.lang.String getUntil(java.lang.String needle,
                                 boolean includeNeedle)
        Collects everything at the start of the string until it encounters the given needle, and returns all that has been collected. This version allows the needle to be included in the returned value, and will position the Chunker instance at the end of the needle. Increments StringChunker position.
        Parameters:
        needle - The target string to search for. Acts as a delimiter.
        includeNeedle - Whether or not to include the needle in the return value
        Returns:
        A String containing every character in the string as well as the needle. If the needle is not found, or it is null, the String will contain every character from the current position of the chunker until the end of the source String.

      • peekUntil

        public java.lang.String peekUntil(java.lang.String needle)
        Collects everything from the current position of the StringChunker until it encounters the given needle, and returns all that has been collected. This version allows the needle to be included in the returned value, and will return the position of the StringChunker to its position prior to the method being invoked.
        Parameters:
        needle - The target string to search for. Acts as a delimiter.
        Returns:
        A String containing every character in the string as well as the needle. If the needle is not found, or it is null, the String will contain every character from the current position of the chunker until the end of the source String.

      • peekUntil

        public java.lang.String peekUntil(java.lang.String needle,
                                  boolean includeNeedle)
        Collects everything at the start of the string until it encounters the given needle, and returns all that has been collected. This version allows the needle to be included in the returned value, and will return the position of the StringChunker to its position prior to the method being invoked.
        Parameters:
        needle - The target string to search for. Acts as a delimiter.
        includeNeedle - Whether or not to include the needle in the return value
        Returns:
        A String containing every character in the string as well as the needle. If the needle is not found, or it is null, the String will contain every character from the current position of the chunker until the end of the source String.

      • getNext

        public java.lang.String getNext(int n)
        Get the next N characters from the source string and return them. If there are not N remaining characters (from the current position of the StringChunker) then the rest of the string will be returned. Increments StringChunker position.
        Parameters:
        n - The number of characters to return from the source String
        Returns:
        If n is less than or equal to the remaining number of characters in the source String, a String of length n containing the following n characters is returned. Otherwise, the remainder of the source String is returned.

      • peekNext

        public java.lang.String peekNext(int n)
        Get the next N characters from the source string and return them. If there are not N remaining characters (from the current position of the StringChunker) then the rest of the string will be returned. Does not affect StringChunker position.
        Parameters:
        n - The number of characters to return from the source String
        Returns:
        If n is less than or equal to the remaining number of characters in the source String, a String of length n containing the following n characters is returned. Otherwise, the remainder of the source String is returned.

      • head

        public java.lang.String head()
        Gets the contents of the source String prior to the current position of the StringChunker
        Returns:
        A String containing all elements of the source string that have already been processed; that is, all characters from the start of the source until the current position of the StringChunker

      • tail

        public java.lang.String tail()
        Gets the remaining content of the source String from the current position of the StringChunker. Does not affect StringChunker position.
        Returns:
        A String containing all elements of the source String from the current position of the StringChunker until the end of the source String
